==English==
===Etymology===
Borrowed from French '''espionnage''', derived from Middle French '''espionner''' meaning "to spy", from Old French '''espion''' meaning "spy", from Italian '''spione''' (from '''spia''')

===Pronunciation===
'ĕs-pē-ŭ-näzh ''also Canadian'' -năzh; -nizh
===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''espionage'''
# The act of learning secret information through [[clandestine]] means.
# undercover work
# [[spying]] or [[reconnaisance]]

